&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About FirstSteps&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The FirstSteps Team is inspired by the belief that every child deserves the opportunity to achieve their fullest potential. To that end, our mission is twofold: to provide the best evidence-based, behavior analytic treatment to our children diagnosed with autism and related learning differences,&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;and&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;to offer a positive, collaborative, and dynamic work experience for our team. We are steadfastly committed&amp;nbsp;to ongoing training and mentorship of our employees, always motivated to support the next generation of clinical leaders in our field and at FirstSteps. Our greatest reward is witnessing the rapid and joyful learning of our little ones and knowing that together, we are creating more happy days for the kids and families we serve.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;1d78qzp&quot; data-start=&quot;158&quot; data-end=&quot;194&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;161&quot; data-end=&quot;194&quot;&gt;Talent Acquisition Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 data-section-id=&quot;mprbmu&quot; data-start=&quot;196&quot; data-end=&quot;218&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;200&quot; data-end=&quot;218&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;219&quot; data-end=&quot;599&quot;&gt;As a Talent Acquisition Specialist, you will play a critical role in building a high-performing clinical team that directly supports the children and families we serve. Reporting to the Director of People &amp;amp; Purpose, you will own full-cycle recruitment for assigned regions, ensuring we attract, hire, and retain top talent to meet both current and future organizational needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;601&quot; data-end=&quot;886&quot;&gt;This role is ideal for someone who is strategic, relationship-driven, and energized by high-volume recruiting in a fast-paced environment. You’ll partner closely with cross-functional leaders to align hiring with operational needs while continuously improving the candidate experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;888&quot; data-end=&quot;1002&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;This is a full-time, in-office position (Monday–Friday, 9:00 AM – 5:30 PM) with occasional overtime as needed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1004&quot; data-end=&quot;1277&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;1004&quot; data-end=&quot;1022&quot;&gt;Work Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br data-start=&quot;1022&quot; data-end=&quot;1025&quot;&gt;This is an in-office role supporting multiple locations. The Talent Acquisition Specialist will have a structured weekly schedule, working on-site at assigned offices (e.g., West Covina, Downey, and Alhambra) to support recruiting needs across regions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1279&quot; data-end=&quot;1471&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;1279&quot; data-end=&quot;1296&quot;&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt; $26–$32/hour, based on experience&lt;br data-start=&quot;1330&quot; data-end=&quot;1333&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;1333&quot; data-end=&quot;1358&quot;&gt;Additional Incentive:&lt;/strong&gt; This role may be eligible for a performance-based bonus plan tied to hiring outcomes and key recruiting metrics.&lt;/p&gt;
